results.definition: fix or set securely or deeply
examples: He planted a knee in the back of his opponent
The dentist implanted a tooth in the gum

results.definition: attach to, as a journalist to a military unit when reporting on a war
examples: The young reporter was embedded with the Third Division

results.definition: enclosed firmly in a surrounding mass
examples: found pebbles embedded in the silt
peach and plum seeds embedded in a sweet edible pulp

results.definition: inserted as an integral part of a surrounding whole
examples: confused by the embedded Latin quotations
